{"ts":"2026-06-12T16:11:27.751Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-3rjo"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Compact strict-create recovery duplicates missing fields under two keys"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"9379cefa (compact strict create recovery) sets both 'missing' and 'missing_required_fields' to the same combinedMissingFlags array in src/cli/commands/create.ts:1541-1545, and renderRecoveryBundle (src/cli/error-guidance.ts) prints BOTH lines, so the compact recovery bundle - whose purpose is token efficiency - emits the identical flag list twice. Repro: in a strict-mode workspace run pm create with a type missing required fields; recovery bundle shows 'missing: --x' and 'missing_required_fields: --x'. Fix options: emit only missing_required_fields in compact mode (drop the legacy 'missing' alias there), or have renderRecoveryBundle suppress missing when missing_required_fields is identical. Also minor: suggested_flags mixes a flag+value token ('--create-mode progressive') with bare flags."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","audit-2026-06-12","token-efficiency"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-12T16:11:27.751Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-12T16:11:27.751Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"20a565aff5033b3d47034a43bea1eb840331f62174711a4328ff6b136258bc1c","message":""}
